trans-unit.source: Azure Active Directory developer's guide

trans-unit.source: Overview
trans-unit.target: Overview

trans-unit.source: As an identity management as a service (IDMaaS) platform, Azure Active Directory provides developers an effective way to integrate identity management into their applications.
trans-unit.target: As an identity management as a service (IDMaaS) platform, Azure Active Directory provides developers an effective way to integrate identity management into their applications.

trans-unit.source: The following articles provide overviews on implementation and key features of Azure Active Directory.
trans-unit.target: The following articles provide overviews on implementation and key features of Azure Active Directory.

trans-unit.source: We suggest that you read them in order, or jump to [Getting started](#getting-started) if you're ready to dig in.
trans-unit.target: We suggest that you read them in order, or jump to [Getting started](#getting-started) if you're ready to dig in.

trans-unit.source: [Integrating with Azure Active Directory](active-directory-how-to-integrate.md): Discover why integration with Azure Active Directory offers the best solution for secure sign-in and authorization.
trans-unit.target: [Integrating with Azure Active Directory](active-directory-how-to-integrate.md): Discover why integration with Azure Active Directory offers the best solution for secure sign-in and authorization.

trans-unit.source: [Active Directory authentication scenarios](active-directory-authentication-scenarios.md): Take advantage of simplified authentication in Azure Active Directory to provide sign-on to your application.
trans-unit.target: [Active Directory authentication scenarios](active-directory-authentication-scenarios.md): Take advantage of simplified authentication in Azure Active Directory to provide sign-on to your application.

trans-unit.source: [Azure Active Directory Graph API](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/hh974476.aspx): Use the Azure Active Directory Graph API to programmatically access Azure Active Directory through REST API endpoints.
trans-unit.target: [Azure Active Directory Graph API](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/hh974476.aspx): Use the Azure Active Directory Graph API to programmatically access Azure Active Directory through REST API endpoints.

trans-unit.source: [Integrating applications in Azure Active Directory](active-directory-integrating-applications.md): Learn about registering your application and the branding guidelines for multitenant applications.
trans-unit.target: [Integrating applications in Azure Active Directory](active-directory-integrating-applications.md): Learn about registering your application and the branding guidelines for multitenant applications.

trans-unit.source: [Azure Active Directory authentication libraries](active-directory-authentication-libraries.md): Easily authenticate users to obtain access tokens by using the Azure authentication libraries.
trans-unit.target: [Azure Active Directory authentication libraries](active-directory-authentication-libraries.md): Easily authenticate users to obtain access tokens by using the Azure authentication libraries.

trans-unit.source: To view Azure Active Directory overviews presented at the Build 2015 conference, see the [Videos](#videos) section below.
trans-unit.target: To view Azure Active Directory overviews presented at the Build 2015 conference, see the [Videos](#videos) section below.

trans-unit.source: Authentication protocols
trans-unit.target: Authentication protocols

trans-unit.source: [SAML 2.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn195591.aspx): The SAML 2.0 protocol enables applications to provide a single sign-on experience to their users.
trans-unit.target: [SAML 2.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn195591.aspx): The SAML 2.0 protocol enables applications to provide a single sign-on experience to their users.

trans-unit.source: [OAuth 2.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn645545.aspx): You can use the OAuth 2.0 protocol to authorize access to web applications and web APIs in your Azure Active Directory tenant.
trans-unit.target: [OAuth 2.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn645545.aspx): You can use the OAuth 2.0 protocol to authorize access to web applications and web APIs in your Azure Active Directory tenant.

trans-unit.source: [OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn645541.aspx): The OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol extends OAuth 2.0 for use as an authentication protocol.
trans-unit.target: [OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn645541.aspx): The OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol extends OAuth 2.0 for use as an authentication protocol.

trans-unit.source: [WS-Federation 1.2 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn903702.aspx): The WS-Federation 1.2 protocol is specified in the Web Services Federation Version 1.2 Specification.
trans-unit.target: [WS-Federation 1.2 protocol reference](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn903702.aspx): The WS-Federation 1.2 protocol is specified in the Web Services Federation Version 1.2 Specification.
